stylometry: The variables you must consider when setting the level of safety stock are the average and variable demand during the lead time.  The average and variable demand can be unpredictable because sometimes the demand can exceed the expected amount.  The lead time and its variability, which lead time is the time is takes for an order to be processed.  The lead time can also be unpredictable because the time it takes for an order to be processed and vary.  Also you must consider the amount of risk of safety stock you are willing to except.  This you can control because its your decision on how much you are willing to except.
